4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under the existing Constitution of Alabama of
6 2022, the state shall not lend money or its credit to
7 any individual, association, or corporation.
8 This bill would propose an amendment to the
9 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to provide that the
10 Alabama Department of Commerce may provide low-interest
11 loans to Alabama automotive manufacturers or suppliers
12 operating in the State of Alabama as part of the
13 Automotive Supply Chain Resilience and Expansion Act.
14
15
16 A BILL
17 TO BE ENTITLED
18 AN ACT
19
20 Proposing an amendment to Section 93 of the
21 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to authorize the Alabama
22 Department of Commerce to provide low-interest loans.
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
24 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
25 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
26 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
27 The following Section 93.19 is added to the
28 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to read as follows:
Page 1

Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to read as follows:
HB549 INTRODUCED
29 The Alabama Department of Commerce is authorized to
30 provide low-interest loans to Alabama automotive manufacturers
31 or suppliers operating in the State of Alabama as part of the
32 Automotive Supply Chain Resilience and Expansion Act.
33 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
34 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
35 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
36 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
37 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
38 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
39 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
40 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
41 language; and translate effective dates.
42 END OF PROPOSED AMENDMENT
43 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
44 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284 and 285 of the
45 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws of this
46 state. The appropriate election official shall assign a ballot
47 number for the proposed constitutional amendment on the
48 election ballot and shall set forth the following description
49 of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
50 constitutional amendment:
51 "Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
52 of 2022, to authorize the Alabama Department of Commerce to
53 provide low-interest loans to Alabama automotive manufacturers
54 or suppliers operating in the State of Alabama as part of the
55 Automotive Supply Chain Resilience and Expansion Act.
56 Proposed by Act ____."
